entries.femaleVariant: [en_us]Hey! I know you! We had a deal!
[en_us]Hey, Ken. Is it time for the next episode "Daddy-Daughter Dilemmas?"
[en_us]Sit. I'll tell you the rest.
[en_us][Sit by Ken.]
[en_us]And she had just called me... a few days before. If only I'd answered...
わかった
[en_us]Fuck... OK. I mean, no one should die alone.
[en_us]What, suddenly realize your priorities ruined your life? No, this is on you. Don't drag me into it.
[en_us]Don't rope me into this.
[en_us]Thank you... But can we do it elsewhere? I have a place.
[en_us]Yes.
[en_us]No.
[en_us]All right.
また後{あと}で
[en_us]Yeah, sure.
[en_us]Can't right now. In a bit of a hurry.
[en_us]And you just had to know everything about me... Had you pegged for a flake.
[en_us]I'm back. Not hurryin' off anywhere else for now.
[en_us]You're just lucky no one took your spot. Have a seat.
[en_us]I'm back.
[en_us]You, come here!
[en_us]Last time, I...I wasn't quite myself. It's starting to happen more often... But that's neither here nor there.
[en_us]Our first conversation made me realize a few things. Strange as it sounds, I want to thank you for being nosy.
[en_us]I'd give it all just to hear her raise her voice again.
[en_us]I'll be back. Maybe.
[en_us]I'll still be here. Maybe.
[en_us]Enid, my baby girl...
[en_us]You deserved it.
それはお気{キ}の{ノ}毒{ドク}
entries.maleVariant: それはお気{キ}の{ノ}毒{ドク}に

entries.femaleVariant: [en_us]Tell me in the car.
[en_us]Happy to be of service.
[en_us]Got a quick tongue, don't you? Just like my Enid... You know, there was a time I thought she was incapable of using a normal tone.
[en_us]Enid's dead, isn't she?
[en_us]Why'd you bite my head off before?
[en_us]Why'd you bite my head off before?
[en_us]Look, you and Enid... You remind me a lot of her.
[en_us]I fooled myself into thinking if you gave me any words of sympathy, forgiveness, it'd be like it came from her.
[en_us]Noticed a lot past tense before. She...she's dead, isn't she?
[en_us]She called me right after she signed her contract. Explained to me that Biotechnica had the DNA for extinct animals she wanted to resurrect.
[en_us]"Platypuses, dad! Platypuses and axolotls! You know I've dreamed of this since elementary school! Ever since you got me that book."
[en_us]I said...I said never wanted to see her again. And hung up.
[en_us]You're a dick.
[en_us]I understand... in a way.
[en_us]Dick move, but I understand the instinct. She knew she picked the enemy over you.
[en_us]Thanks for the reminder all corpos are massive dickheads.
[en_us]I broke off contact, not wanting to know what she did, where she lived. She betrayed the company... and, by extension, me.
[en_us]I know...I know! I was just so furious, I lost myself... How could I know it would be the last time I'd hear her voice?
[en_us]That call still haunts my sleep... How could I know it would be the last time I'd hear her voice?
[en_us]Whoever isn't with us is against us... Classic.
[en_us]Don't you mock me. Not right now.
[en_us]Then, one day the CEO called me in to talk. I thought he wanted to talk strategy for the upcoming quarter...
[en_us]But as soon as I stepped in, he told me he had Enid  killed.
[en_us]Why do it, have her killed?
[en_us]Competition? To test my loyalty, maybe?
[en_us]Enid focused on artificial tissues, regenerative work... heart muscle.
[en_us]If Biotechnica took it to market, Kendachi pacemaker sales... they would have plummeted.
[en_us]Jesus, Ken, I'm sorry... You fucked up, but not enough to deserve this.
[en_us]Don't know what you expected after sellin' yourself to a corp. One day you're destroying lives, next it's yours. Circle of life.
[en_us]Why have Enid killed?
[en_us]Your words won't change anything. Still... thank you. I mean it.
[en_us]I didn't deserve that. I did everything for her! Everything!
[en_us]You really so fuckin' certain?
[en_us]Guessin' we're at the part we agreed on. What is it you want from me for your story? Revenge?
[en_us]I would've killed him.
[en_us]I'd have gutted the bastard. Dont' care if his security flatlined me after.
[en_us]When the initial shock passed, I thought of nothing else. I had to wipe that arrogant smirk from his face.
[en_us]So I threw myself at him in a rage. If only I had mantis blades instead of my bare hands...
[en_us]Finally, a good decision. Only a shame it came too late.
[en_us]They didn't kill me, though. Would've been a bad PR move. Instead they waited – waited until I wound up here.
[en_us]Just... kill me. That's it.
[en_us]I have no strength left, and I don't want it back. I don't even have enough to pull the trigger.
[en_us]Wait, please! You can't leave me like this now!
[en_us]No? Watch me.
[en_us]Last one had quite the dramatic conclusion.
[en_us][Offer Ken a cigarette.]
[en_us]I don't smoke.
[en_us]Here. To cool your nerves?
[en_us]Out of luck. Don't smoke.
[en_us]Got a cigarette? It's a perfect day for a puff.
[en_us]For our history lesson.
[en_us]New day, new disappointments... It's fine.
